  "short_text": "String to Tuple",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a string as input and converts it into a tuple where each character of the string is an element of the tuple.\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\n- The input will be a single string.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\n- Print the tuple where each character of the string is an element of the tuple.\n\n---\n\n#### Example\n\nIf the input string is `Hello`, the output should be:\n\n```\n('H', 'e', 'l', 'l', 'o')\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
